living with her in-laws?

93
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:27,239
Oh, my. You still seem to be lost
in dreamland.

94
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:30,239
Look here. Please wake up, will you?

95
00:06:30,239 --> 00:06:32,479
Who is getting married?

96
00:06:34,650 --> 00:06:36,409
What's all this noise?

97
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:39,179
- Oh, you're here, Ms. Jung.
- Hey.

98
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,750
We've met, haven't we?

99
00:06:42,349 --> 00:06:45,289
It's good to see you.
I'm Ji Na's mom.

100
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:50,159
Come in.

101
00:06:54,770 --> 00:06:56,630
You...

102
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:58,640
Are you done making fresh kimchi?

103
00:06:58,969 --> 00:07:00,599
You must've finished quickly.

104
00:07:07,179 --> 00:07:11,820
Ma'am, thank you
for inviting us to your home.

105
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:14,620
Oh, yes. I see you're already here.

106
00:07:26,659 --> 00:07:27,669
Gong Hee.

107
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,400
Here's some medicine
for indigestion.

108
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:32,570
What?

109
00:07:33,339 --> 00:07:35,969
I noticed you seemed to have
an upset stomach this morning.

110
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:40,109
You don't look so great.

111
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:43,750
You have a lot on your plate.
Things are tough, aren't they?

112
00:07:45,179 --> 00:07:46,320
It's not like that.

113
00:07:47,380 --> 00:07:50,049
Then do you have
some other kind of concern?

114
00:07:52,690 --> 00:07:55,190
I attached the sonogram picture
under today's date.

115
00:07:55,729 --> 00:07:57,029
You should show that
to the baby's father.

116
00:07:57,029 --> 00:07:58,159
I'm sure he'll be happy.

117
00:08:03,229 --> 00:08:04,299
You can tell me.

118
00:08:07,370 --> 00:08:08,539
It's nothing.

119
00:08:09,310 --> 00:08:11,239
Let me know anytime
if it gets to be too much.

120
00:08:11,979 --> 00:08:14,010
The burden will weigh a little less
if we share it.

121
00:08:18,580 --> 00:08:19,620
Gong Hee,

122
00:08:20,919 --> 00:08:22,750
you're such an amazing person.

123
00:08:26,789 --> 00:08:29,560
Should I say you're like
an legendary sword in its sheath?

124
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:34,330
People don't know
how sharp you are yet,

125
00:08:35,229 --> 00:08:36,299
but once you show yourself,

126
00:08:37,029 --> 00:08:38,700
anyone will recognize you.

127
00:08:39,140 --> 00:08:41,409
Just how great a person you are...

128
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:43,609
and how talented you are
as a designer.

129
00:08:46,510 --> 00:08:47,710
Thank you.

130
00:09:30,919 --> 00:09:33,189
Oh, my. Mother.

131
00:09:34,189 --> 00:09:37,059
What are you doing in here?

132
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,230
Myung Ja...

133
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:43,069
She must feel very lonely.

134
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:46,270
Our children think...

135
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:49,970
they've only left us physically,

136
00:09:50,709 --> 00:09:52,480
but from a mother's heart,

137
00:09:52,579 --> 00:09:54,850
it's as if
a pillar has gone missing.

138
00:09:56,209 --> 00:09:58,319
It hurts so much...

139
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:01,520
that it makes you
fall to the ground.

140
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:06,520
But it's not like
he's going anywhere far.

141
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:09,159
Whether it's far or close,

142
00:10:11,529 --> 00:10:13,829
that's how it feels
when your kids move out...

143
00:10:14,829 --> 00:10:15,829
with all their things.

144
00:10:17,569 --> 00:10:20,770
You think,
"Now, they must be really leaving."

145
00:10:22,439 --> 00:10:25,579
It's like a cold wind blowing
through your heart.

146
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:28,480
All right. Come in.

147
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,480
What?

148
00:10:34,350 --> 00:10:35,350
Wait.

149
00:10:36,090 --> 00:10:37,090
What?

150
00:10:37,590 --> 00:10:38,890
Is that you, Gong Boo?

151
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:42,029
You just left. Why are you back?

152
00:10:42,029 --> 00:10:45,130
Didn't you go to your new home?

153
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:48,970
Well, I'm in a bit of a pickle.

154
00:10:50,299 --> 00:10:52,169
- What?
- Come in.

155
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,939
Who are you?

156
00:11:00,579 --> 00:11:02,679
I'm Maeng No Ah.

157
00:11:02,679 --> 00:11:03,750
Oh, boy.

158
00:11:05,179 --> 00:11:06,919
"Maeng No Ah?"

159
00:11:08,020 --> 00:11:11,760
I am Maeng Gong Boo's son.

160
00:11:17,590 --> 00:11:19,630
Dad, let me talk to Soo Yeon.

161
00:11:19,630 --> 00:11:20,900
Please watch him.

162
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:24,329
Wait, is this really your son?

163
00:11:24,329 --> 00:11:27,000
Anyway, this is an emergency.

164
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,970
Soo Yeon seems to be dropping
a nuclear bomb on me.

165
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:31,039
Wait, what is going on?

166
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:32,480
If I can't figure this out,

167
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,740
my life
and my marriage will be over.

168
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,380
I'll be right back.
See you in a bit!

169
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,480
Oh, dear.

170
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:48,730
The button just fell right off.

171
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:50,890
I can't sew this back on.

172
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:52,429
You need to use the machine
to put this back on.

173
00:11:53,929 --> 00:11:54,929
And...

174
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:58,199
I brought this.
Can you let out the waist?

175
00:11:58,199 --> 00:12:00,470
My goodness. I don't even eat much,

176
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:03,240
so I don't understand
why I keep gaining belly fat.

177
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,240
Am I pregnant or something?

178
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:08,079
I can fix these quickly.

179
00:12:08,650 --> 00:12:09,650
Give me a few minutes.

180
00:12:11,449 --> 00:12:12,449
Ladies.

181
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:18,020
Do you still talk to Dan Soo?

182
00:12:18,319 --> 00:12:19,319
Dan Soo?

183
00:12:20,189 --> 00:12:21,789
You must've heard the news.

184
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:23,130
I told her.

185
00:12:24,189 --> 00:12:25,429
You and your big mouth.

186
00:12:26,929 --> 00:12:29,169
He moved back
to his grandmother's house.

187
00:12:29,169 --> 00:12:30,630
Why? Did you need to talk to him
about something?

188
00:12:32,699 --> 00:12:35,069
He said he'd visit us
to say goodbye in person,

189
00:12:35,069 --> 00:12:36,909
but we haven't seen him.
I guess he's busy.

190
00:12:36,909 --> 00:12:39,140
I assumed
he must be busy or something,

191
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,439
so I haven't tried calling him yet.

192
00:12:42,809 --> 00:12:43,949
Then could you...

193
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:46,819
give me his number?

194
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,490
Oh, sure. I'll give you his number.

195
00:12:52,789 --> 00:12:53,789
(Gyeong Tae)

196
00:12:53,789 --> 00:12:54,789
One moment.

197
00:12:55,130 --> 00:12:56,230
(Gyeong Tae)

198
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:58,400
Hi.

199
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:01,630
