00:16:40,279 --> 00:16:42,789
I'm heading
to the departure gate now.

264
00:16:42,789 --> 00:16:43,789
You...

265
00:16:45,289 --> 00:16:46,289
Hey.

266
00:16:46,919 --> 00:16:48,959
Who's that kid? Who is he?

267
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:52,199
He's your son.

268
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:56,600
You saw the DNA test report, right?

269
00:16:57,029 --> 00:16:59,900
But how?
I mean, when did this happen?

270
00:17:00,539 --> 00:17:02,270
We split up
just a month after our wedding.

271
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:04,209
How's it possible that
you got pregnant, all of a sudden?

272
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:07,340
I raised him by myself
for the past five years.

273
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:09,750
I'm participating in this two-year
training program in the US.

274
00:17:10,409 --> 00:17:11,650
You can't take care of him
for two years?

275
00:17:12,779 --> 00:17:14,620
It's about time
you played your role as his father.

276
00:17:17,789 --> 00:17:19,260
Hey, Lee Soo Yeon!

277
00:17:20,459 --> 00:17:22,590
My gosh. This was
a premeditated nuclear attack.

278
00:17:23,159 --> 00:17:24,999
- Where is she now?
- She's at the airport.

279
00:17:25,699 --> 00:17:27,360
I get that she's joining
a training program in the US,

280
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:29,400
but why does she have to
drop this bomb on me?

281
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,669
Seriously, Lee Soo Yeon!
I can't believe this.

282
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,310
Why, you...

283
00:17:37,409 --> 00:17:40,540
Goodness. Oh, boy.

284
00:17:42,209 --> 00:17:45,050
Ji Na,
am I making you uncomfortable?

285
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:48,489
Why aren't you eating?

286
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:51,890
Oh, she's always like this.

287
00:17:51,890 --> 00:17:53,390
She's on a diet.

288
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,390
Now that
Dan Soo has moved back home,

289
00:17:57,390 --> 00:18:02,370
I think we should expedite things.
That's why I called you here.

290
00:18:02,929 --> 00:18:06,169
The merger of Dodo Group
and Jayce Group...

291
00:18:06,570 --> 00:18:07,699
through this marriage.

292
00:18:11,739 --> 00:18:13,009
You're still talking about this?

293
00:18:13,439 --> 00:18:15,179
Grandma, your wish has been granted.
Am I wrong?

294
00:18:15,449 --> 00:18:16,449
My wish?

295
00:18:17,979 --> 00:18:22,050
Me. Your dear grandson,
Gu Dan Soo, is back.

296
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:24,120
Is that not enough for you?
Now, I have to get married?

297
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:26,120
I have to marry her, of all women?

298
00:18:27,390 --> 00:18:28,989
I heard
you were taking time off work.

299
00:18:28,989 --> 00:18:30,689
I didn't expect to see you here.

300
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,959
This is my home.
Why can't I be here?

301
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:37,870
Well, I was talking about the place
where you used to live.

302
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,739
I guess things didn't work out
between you and your roommate.

303
00:18:43,370 --> 00:18:44,880
I heard...

304
00:18:45,679 --> 00:18:47,640
Dan Soo was renting a room
from a family.

305
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:50,179
What do you mean he had a roommate?

306
00:18:51,050 --> 00:18:54,050
What about you?
You have a boyfriend.

307
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:55,390
What are you doing here?

308
00:18:56,290 --> 00:18:57,390
Oh, I see.

309
00:18:57,949 --> 00:18:59,360
You want to marry me...

310
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:01,189
and keep dating him?

311
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:06,100
You have a boyfriend?

312
00:19:06,300 --> 00:19:09,400
What? A boyfriend?
What are you talking about?

313
00:19:09,669 --> 00:19:13,640
Ji Na isn't seeing anyone else,
ma'am.

314
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,840
Is your mother telling the truth?

315
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:21,409
Are you sure
you're not seeing someone else?

316
00:19:23,749 --> 00:19:25,050
Tell her the truth.

317
00:19:28,989 --> 00:19:30,120
I will...

318
00:19:31,390 --> 00:19:33,259
tell you everything later, ma'am.

319
00:19:50,669 --> 00:19:52,380
How could you say that
in front of Chairwoman Hwang?

320
00:19:53,110 --> 00:19:54,810
Gu Dan Soo. Can you not think?

321
00:19:55,449 --> 00:19:57,350
Aren't you the one who can't think?

322
00:19:57,850 --> 00:19:59,150
Why did you come here?

323
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:02,090
I heard you said you wanted
to break off the engagement.

324
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:04,419
Was it all a lie?

325
00:20:04,419 --> 00:20:06,090
I'll figure out what to do.

326
00:20:06,090 --> 00:20:07,659
It's none of your business.

327
00:20:09,459 --> 00:20:10,630
Does Min Gi know...

328
00:20:11,489 --> 00:20:13,530
that you're here now?

329
00:20:15,469 --> 00:20:16,530
My gosh.

330
00:20:17,469 --> 00:20:21,239
I was really disappointed in Min Gi,

331
00:20:21,909 --> 00:20:23,610
but I suddenly feel bad for him.

332
00:20:24,739 --> 00:20:26,110
He dumped his girlfriend,

333
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:27,909
saying he was in love
with someone else.

334
00:20:28,380 --> 00:20:30,280
But now, he's about to get dumped.

335
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,679
The greedy Kang Ji Na
played him for a fool.

336
00:20:36,620 --> 00:20:38,019
Eat up.

337
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:42,290
Children must eat well.

338
00:20:42,459 --> 00:20:44,259
Okay, Great-grandma.

339
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:46,800
Here.

340
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:48,530
I...

341
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,130
can eat on my own.

342
00:21:03,610 --> 00:21:05,580
I have a nephew now?

343
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,179
That's right.

344
00:21:07,419 --> 00:21:10,290
He came wearing his DNA test report
around his neck.

345
00:21:10,590 --> 00:21:12,459
Come on. We don't even need proof.

346
00:21:12,459 --> 00:21:14,290
He looks just like Gong Boo
when Gong Boo was little.

347
00:21:14,489 --> 00:21:16,489
Oh, no. This is huge.

348
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:18,959
Soo Yeon has been raising him
all this time?

349
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:20,860
Who knows?

350
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:22,729
Maybe she had him
with another man...

351
00:21:22,729 --> 00:21:25,400
and left him here
before she took off.

352
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,570
Gyeong Bok, why would you say that?

353
00:21:27,870 --> 00:21:29,409
It's a good thing
that he came to us.

354
00:21:29,409 --> 00:21:30,570
Besides, he is Gong Boo's child.

355
00:21:30,570 --> 00:21:31,669
Gosh, you...

356
00:21:32,540 --> 00:21:34,810
When he got married,
I thought that was it.

357
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:38,050
How many problems
will his first marriage cause?

358
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:41,219
Who knew this would happen
right after their honeymoon?

359
00:21:41,719 --> 00:21:44,350
How could Soo Yeon do this?

360
00:21:46,959 --> 00:21:50,060
Soo Yeon must've been through a lot
to raise the kid on her own.

361
00:21:50,729 --> 00:21:53,330
Did we force her
to raise him on her own?

362
00:21:53,330 --> 00:21:54,729
It's not like we kicked her out.

363
00:21:54,729 --> 00:21:55,870
She's the one who left.

364
00:21:55,870 --> 00:21:57,900
She created this whole mess.

365
00:21:58,669 --> 00:21:59,969
Goodness.

366
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,610
Where has Gong Boo gone?

367
00:22:02,610 --> 00:22:05,979
Oh, whatever. Who knows
if he's dead or alive? Good grief.

368
00:22:05,979 --> 00:22:08,909
We should be grateful if his wife
hasn't beaten him to death.

369
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:11,479
They just had their wedding
and got back from their honeymoon...

370
00:22:11,479 --> 00:22:12,550
only to be met
with his ex-wife's kid?

371
00:22:12,550 --> 00:22:14,050
Gosh, we're lucky she didn't faint.

372
00:22:17,850 --> 00:22:20,320
My goodness.

373
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:30,769
You said you weren't lying to me
about anything else!

374
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:34,070
You said you didn't have
any more secrets!

375
00:22:34,070 --> 00:22:37,570
I swear, I didn't know about this.

376
00:22:37,570 --> 00:22:39,840
You giant onion!

377
00:22:40,580 --> 00:22:43,350
I keep peeling you open,

378
00:22:44,709 --> 00:22:47,620
but there's always something more.
What should I do?

379
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:51,689
But I really didn't know...

380
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:56,189
Get out! Leave.

381
00:22:56,189 --> 00:22:58,360
Get out of my sight
right this instant. Leave!

382
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:02,870
- I'm sorry, honey.
- Get out!

383
00:23:02,870 --> 00:23:04,900
- No, but I...
- Get out.

384
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:06,340
- Okay. Wait.
- Get out!

385
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:10,239
Hong Dan!

386
00:23:10,769 --> 00:23:11,780
Honey!

387
00:23:13,979 --> 00:23:15,479
I'm not moving an inch from here.

388
00:23:15,479 --> 00:23:16,850
I'll wait all night long.

389
00:23:17,679 --> 00:23:19,479
Until you let me in,

390
00:23:19,479 --> 00:23:21,080
I will be on my knees
with my arms...

391
00:23:23,449 --> 00:23:24,550
I knew it.

392
00:23:24,919 --> 00:23:26,259
I knew you'd let me back in.

393
00:23:30,729 --> 00:23:31,729
But Hong Dan...

394
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,229
(No one from the Maeng family
is allowed inside!)

395
00:23:56,050 --> 00:23:57,050
You're here.

396
00:23:59,189 --> 00:24:01,320
Don't you know
how busy we are at work these days?

397
00:24:01,759 --> 00:24:03,459
What are you doing?
Why aren't you coming to work?

398
00:24:04,989 --> 00:24:06,199
Can't you see?

399
00:24:06,699 --> 00:24:08,669
I'm back to where I used to be.

400
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,999
I've moved back home,

401
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:14,540
and I'm back to being a slacker
who plays around all day.

402
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:22,249
At least look at me
if you called me over.

403
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:25,820
You said you had something to say.
What is it?

404
00:24:27,419 --> 00:24:29,620
Ms. Kang was just here.

405
00:24:30,189 --> 00:24:32,719
She came here for dinner
with her mom.

406
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:37,130
I guess you didn't know.

407
00:24:37,659 --> 00:24:39,300
Gosh, it's obvious.

408
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:41,600
She couldn't help but come
because Grandma insisted.

409
00:24:50,370 --> 00:24:51,909
Make your position clear.

410
00:24:52,340 --> 00:24:53,880
You're the one
who abandoned Gong Hee...

411
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,479
and chose Kang Ji Na.

412
00:24:56,449 --> 00:24:58,749
What did you tell me
when we were young?

413
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:01,050
"Be decisive when making choices."

414
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,449
"Be sure to take responsibility."

415
00:25:03,850 --> 00:25:04,850
You know,

416
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,890
I thought
you looked so cool back then.

417
00:25:08,759 --> 00:25:09,830
But...

418
00:25:10,689 --> 00:25:13,130
why is it that Seo Min Gi
doesn't look cool at all anymore?

419
00:25:15,130 --> 00:25:16,800
If you made a decisive choice,

420
00:25:17,330 --> 00:25:18,669
take responsibility for it as well.

421
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:25,640
Don't let me down anymore...

422
00:25:26,110 --> 00:25:27,810
while I still consider you
my friend.

423
00:25:30,509 --> 00:25:32,080
You could've said this
over the phone.

424
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:33,780
Why are you making me come and go?

425
00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:36,919
You'll have to come to me
whenever I call you from now on.

426
00:25:38,290 --> 00:25:39,290
What?

427
00:25:41,989 --> 00:25:44,259
Come and report to me
on what's going on at work.

428
00:25:44,959 --> 00:25:46,699
I don't need to know
about anything else.

429
00:25:46,830 --> 00:25:49,229
Just report to me
about the fashion show.

430
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:50,830
I think I should know.

431
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:55,640
You're unbelievable.

432
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:59,009
You took time off work
because you just felt like it.

433
00:25:59,310 --> 00:26:00,610
So why are you curious
about what goes on at work?

434
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:02,580
What are you planning on doing?

435
00:26:03,580 --> 00:26:05,719
Forget it. I'm done talking.

436
00:26:06,719 --> 00:26:07,949
I have nothing more to say.

437
00:26:07,949 --> 00:26:09,650
You can go or whatever.

438
00:26:31,739 --> 00:26:33,340
Hey, Gu Dan Soo!

439
00:26:34,939 --> 00:26:36,780
Without you here,

440
00:26:37,479 --> 00:26:40,679
I don't have anyone
to eat late-night snacks with!

441
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:43,489
Why do I have to order so much...

442
00:26:43,489 --> 00:26:45,759
just to have some tteokbokki
delivered?

443
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:49,229
I don't have anyone to go
to the convenience store with...

444
00:26:49,229 --> 00:26:51,530
even when I'm scared
to go out alone at night!

445
00:26:52,759 --> 00:26:54,860
You said to lean on you
when things were hard!

446
00:26:55,699 --> 00:26:58,100
You said
you'd always stay by my side!

447
00:26:59,439 --> 00:27:01,070
So why did you leave?

448
00:27:01,439 --> 00:27:03,840
You should be by my side, at least!

449
00:27:05,580 --> 00:27:07,239
How could you leave like that...

450
00:27:07,239 --> 00:27:10,009
just because I got a little angry?

451
00:27:14,780 --> 00:27:15,949
Why do I feel so frustrated...

452
00:27:16,719 --> 00:27:19,719
no matter how much I yell?

453
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:27,530
Gu Dan Soo!

454
00:27:27,999 --> 00:27:30,769
Hey! You jerk!

455
00:27:31,199 --> 00:27:33,900
Gu Dan Soo, you total fraud!

456
00:27:34,269 --> 00:27:35,439
Hey!

457
00:27:36,009 --> 00:27:37,009
Why are you calling me?

458
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:08,070
Gu Dan Soo, you...

459
00:28:09,669 --> 00:28:10,870
I'm right here.

460
00:28:23,350 --> 00:28:25,959
(My Merry Marriage)

461
00:28:25,959 --> 00:28:27,290
There's something you don't know.

462
00:28:27,290 --> 00:28:28,830
I wasn't just friends with you.

463
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:30,060
You were my first love.

464
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:31,189
Hey, Gu Dan Soo.

465
00:28:31,189 --> 00:28:33,600
Friends? That won't cut it for me.

466
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,060
I want to become more than that.

467
00:28:35,060 --> 00:28:36,300
Arms in the air.

468
00:28:36,300 --> 00:28:38,229
I can change myself.

469
00:28:38,229 --> 00:28:41,769
Mom told me
that I should get changed on my own.

470
00:28:41,769 --> 00:28:43,110
Didn't your mom
tell you anything else?

471
00:28:43,340 --> 00:28:46,179
Ssook Ssook,
you don't have a daddy anymore.

472
00:28:46,179 --> 00:28:48,739
Do you know how I was treated today?

473
00:28:48,739 --> 00:28:50,009
I'll put things right.

474
00:28:50,009 --> 00:28:52,280
I'll put everything back
to where they should be.

475
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,050
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
